]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>While Google still dominates the search industry, AI platforms like ChatGPT, Perplexity, Copilot, and Gemini are taking slices of the pie. And those slices could eventually have a big impact on traditional search traffic.</p>
<p>You might have even started to see some website visits trickle through from AI in your analytics. As more and more businesses see a decline in organic traffic, looking for new sources&#8211;like AI referral traffic&#8211;will become more important. Want to get started? Follow these tips to help drive referral traffic from AI search and measure results.</p>
<h3>Contents</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="#what-is-ai-referral-traffic">What is AI referral traffic (and why it matters)</a></li>
<li><a href="#how-to-get-more-ai-referral-traffic">How to get more referral traffic from AI search</a>
<ol>
<li><a href="#make-it-easy-for-ai-crawlers">Make it easy for AI crawlers to find content on your site</a></li>
<li><a href="#target-conversational-queries">Target conversational queries</a></li>
<li><a href="#improve-e-e-a-t-signals">Improve the E-E-A-T signals of your content</a></li>
<li><a href="#earn-more-brand-mentions">Earn more brand mentions on the web</a></li>
<li><a href="#optimize-for-featured-snippets">Optimize for featured snippets and AI Overviews</a></li>
<li><a href="#adapt-content-strategy-for-ai-platforms">Adapt your content strategy for specific AI platforms</a></li>
</ol>
</li>
<li><a href="#how-to-track-ai-referral-traffic">How to track AI referral traffic</a></li>
</ul>
<div id="what-is-ai-referral-traffic"></div>
<h2>What is AI referral traffic (and why it matters)</h2>
<p>AI referral traffic is any traffic driven by an AI tool or platform. This includes ChatGPT, Perplexity, or any other platforms we mentioned earlier.</p>
<p>As more people use <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/chatgpt-search" rel="noopener">AI search engines</a> to find information, and as more AI search engines pop up, you have the opportunity to <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/drive-more-traffic-to-your-website/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">drive traffic</a> from those searches.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/ai-referral-traffic-example-chatgpt-png.webp" alt="example of chatgpt search with referral traffic potential" width="1200" height="876" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-90002" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/ai-referral-traffic-example-chatgpt-png.webp 1200w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/ai-referral-traffic-example-chatgpt-980x715.webp 980w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/ai-referral-traffic-example-chatgpt-480x350.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1200px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>In the example above, we searched for how to fix a sink leak on ChatGPT, and it provided this <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/llm-tracking">list of sources</a>. From here, we could click off to one of the source links to get more information about our inquiry.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f916.png" alt="ü§ñ" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>Are you using AI the right way?</strong> Free download &gt;&gt; <a href="https://marketing.localiq.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsiteAIinMarketingGuide.html?cid=Web_Any_BlogInContent_PPC_AIMarketing_Download">Emergency Guide to AI in Marketing</a></p>
<div id="how-to-get-more-ai-referral-traffic"></div>
<h2>6 ways to get more referral traffic from AI search</h2>
<p>Try these tips to see more <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/11/29/referral-traffic" rel="noopener">referral traffic</a> from AI search to your website.</p>
<div id="make-it-easy-for-ai-crawlers"></div>
<h3>1. Make it easy for AI crawlers to find content on your site</h3>
<p>AI crawlers (or spiders) sift through an endless supply of pages on the web, trying to match users with the most relevant content. If your site is slow or hard to navigate, you‚Äôre basically presenting crawlers (and users, for that matter) with a mess.</p>
<p>Here‚Äôs how to make it easy:</p>
<h4>Improve page speed and mobile friendliness</h4>
<p>Page speed is a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/09/09/google-ranking-factors" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google ranking factor</a>, so your site needs to load fast for Google. But it should also be fast for AI. Crawlers are built to scan and summarize content quickly, and there‚Äôs a chance they might time out and not fully crawl everything if your site is slow.</p>
<p>Google‚Äôs <a href="https://pagespeed.web.dev/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Page Speed Insights</a> tool makes it easy to see how fast your pages load and what elements can be addressed. Simply plug in the URL of the page you want speed insights for and get results in just seconds.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/pagespeed-insights-tool-example-results-png.webp" alt="example report for google pagespeed insights tool" width="1200" height="853" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-90003" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/pagespeed-insights-tool-example-results-png.webp 1200w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/pagespeed-insights-tool-example-results-980x697.webp 980w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/pagespeed-insights-tool-example-results-480x341.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1200px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Some quick fixes:</p>
<ul>
<li>Compress images with tools like <a href="https://tinyjpg.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TinyPNG</a> or <a href="https://squoosh.app/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Squoosh</a></li>
<li>Try using lazy loading</li>
<li>Use a content delivery network (CDN) to speed up load times globally</li>
<li>Eliminate unnecessary plugins and scripts. If your site is running five different tracking codes, it might be time to clean things up.</li>
</ul>
<p>Your site also needs to be mobile-friendly, and the most common way to achieve this is through responsive web design. A responsive site automatically adjusts your page sizes, layout, button types, and more to work better on mobile devices.</p>
<p>Plus, AI search is built to answer questions on the go, whether someone‚Äôs using voice search in a car or scrolling through results on their phone. If and when you show up in AI search results, you don‚Äôt want visitors to arrive at a clunky design.</p>
<h4>Use internal links for optimal crawlability and discoverability</h4>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/05/04/internal-linking" rel="noopener">Internal links</a> connect different pages of your website, making it easier for AI crawlers to navigate between them. These links also help the crawlers find all the content on your site. If a page exists without any links pointing to it (i.e., it‚Äôs an orphan page), a crawler might not see it.</p>
<p>You can add internal links in your navigation, footers, within each piece of content, and in other places.</p>
<p>As the crawlers move through your site, they collect more information about your content that influences whether or not you‚Äôll be mentioned and listed in AI results. Internal links have great benefits for <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/07/27/seo-metrics" rel="noopener">SEO performance</a>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/how-web-crawlers-work-png.webp" alt="graphic showing how web crawlers work" width="676" height="510" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-90004" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/how-web-crawlers-work-png.webp 676w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/how-web-crawlers-work-480x362.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 676px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>A well-linked site helps AI understand the relationships between your content, making it easier for the platforms to cite your pages when users search topics related to your site.</p>
<p><strong>Tip: </strong>Make sure you can reach any page of your site in three clicks or fewer from any other page. One way to do this is through <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/topic-clusters-for-local-seo">topic clusters</a>.</p>
<div id="target-conversational-queries"></div>
<h3>2. Target conversational queries</h3>
<p><a href="https://backlinko.com/google-keyword-study" target="_blank" rel="noopener">91%</a> of all search queries are considered long tail, or conversational. Sure, people still search broad terms like ‚Äúgarden hoses.‚Äù But with AI, people talk to it like they would a friend, asking questions like:</p>
<ul>
<li>What‚Äôs the best garden hose that won‚Äôt kink?</li>
<li>Which hose is best for a big backyard?</li>
</ul>
<p>Tools like ChatGPT, Perplexity, and Copilot can generate ideas and variations of how users ask about a topic. Even though these don‚Äôt have actual search data (like volume or intent), the ideas can still be worth considering since they come from AI itself‚Äìthe very place you want to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/offset-lower-website-traffic">get traffic</a> from.</p>
<p>For example, instead of targeting just ‚Äúgarden hoses‚Äù in your content, ask an <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-tools-for-marketing-agency">AI tool</a> to provide questions and conversational phrases about the topic. You might get responses like:</p>
<ul>
<li>What‚Äôs the best garden hose for water pressure?</li>
<li>Which garden hose lasts the longest?</li>
<li>What size hose do I need for my yard?</li>
</ul>
<p>AI search engines will return clear, direct answers in response to conversational queries. So, your page content should do the same.</p>
<p>Also consider the ‚ÄúPeople also ask‚Äù (PAA) section in Google results for more ideas. Google practically hands you a roadmap to conversational search. The PAA section lists related questions you can use and answer in your content.</p>
<p>As an example, when I search ‚Äúgarden hoses,‚Äù this is what the PAA section shows. And when I click on a question, even more questions will appear at the bottom of the list.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/people-also-ask-results-garden-hoses-png.webp" alt="example of people also ask results for garden hoses query" width="903" height="286" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-90005" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/people-also-ask-results-garden-hoses-png.webp 903w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/people-also-ask-results-garden-hoses-480x152.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 903px, 100vw" /></p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f50e.png" alt="üîé" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>Need help finding the right keywords?</strong> Try our <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/keywords?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_Keywords_KWTool">Free Keyword Tool</a>!</p>
<div id="improve-e-e-a-t-signals"></div>
<h3>3. Improve the E-E-A-T signals of your content</h3>
<p>A <a href="https://www.seerinteractive.com/insights/what-drives-brand-mentions-in-ai-answers" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Seer Interactive study</a> about what drives brand visibility in AI answers showed that brands ranking on the first page of Google have a strong correlation.</p>
<p>And when they filtered the data to focus on solution-oriented websites, there was an even stronger correlation, proving that quality content is important.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/llm-mentions-by-serp-factor-seer-study-png.webp" alt="seer study results showing correlation of LLM mentions by serp factor" width="996" height="549" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-90006" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/llm-mentions-by-serp-factor-seer-study-png.webp 996w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/llm-mentions-by-serp-factor-seer-study-980x540.webp 980w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/llm-mentions-by-serp-factor-seer-study-480x265.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 996px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://www.seerinteractive.com/insights/what-drives-brand-mentions-in-ai-answers" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Source</a></em></p>
<p>What does that mean for you?</p>
<p>To <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/09/05/chatgpt-seo">rank high in search engines</a>, and thus appear in AI search, your content needs to be the most reliable, well-supported option for the topic. And this is where <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/07/14/google-e-e-a-t" rel="noopener">E-E-A-T</a> comes in: Experience, Expertise, Authoritativeness, and Trustworthiness. These are the guidelines Google uses to evaluate content quality.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/google-eeat.webp" alt="definition of google e-eat" width="918" height="580" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-90007" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/google-eeat.webp 918w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/google-eeat-480x303.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 918px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Thin, basic content doesn‚Äôt cut it. AI search prioritizes content that fully answers someone‚Äôs query.</p>
<p>Let‚Äôs say you sell project management software, and you‚Äôre creating a comparison piece titled ‚ÄúTop 10 Project Management Tools.‚Äù Instead of just listing the tools with a description and price for each, you should aim to stand out by putting together helpful, in-depth information that‚Äôs backed by data and reputable sources.</p>
<p>For the article, you could improve its E-E-A-T signals by:</p>
<ul>
<li>Including side-by-side feature comparisons (e.g., how the tools stack up for workflow automation).</li>
<li>Sharing common pitfalls to avoid, like failing to onboard your team properly.</li>
<li>Tailoring recommendations for freelancers, startups, and enterprises.</li>
<li>Using stats with cited sources.</li>
<li>Quoting industry experts.</li>
<li>Referencing <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/04/03/how-to-write-a-case-study">case studies</a> to back up claims.</li>
<li>Using images and videos to support concepts.</li>
</ul>
<div id="earn-more-brand-mentions"></div>
<h3>4. Earn more brand mentions on the web</h3>
<p><a href="https://writings.stephenwolfram.com/2023/02/what-is-chatgpt-doing-and-why-does-it-work/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stephen Wolfram wrote</a> that ChatGPT ‚Äúlooks for things that in a certain sense match in meaning.‚Äù It‚Äôs trained based on what it has learned from the web.</p>
<p>And <a href="https://sparktoro.com/blog/how-can-my-brand-appear-in-answers-from-chatgpt-perplexity-gemini-and-other-ai-llm-tools/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Rand Fishkin of SparkToro created a video</a> about large language models (LLMs) using mentions as their currency.</p>
<p>So, to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/12/10/link-building-secrets">get links</a> and traffic from LLMs, you need to get your brand mentioned on sites that cover topics related to your business. You want to signal to AI that you‚Äôre a notable brand in your space.</p>
<p>If you sell project management software, Google some of your target keywords and see what ranks. Reach out to those sites to:</p>
<ul>
<li>Engage with industry blogs and media. Get featured in ‚ÄúTop 10‚Äù roundups and sponsored features.</li>
<li>Collaborate with well-known project management experts on webinars, podcasts, or guest blog posts.</li>
<li>Cross-promote with complementary brands. Team up with a time-tracking app or collaboration tool.</li>
</ul>
<div id="optimize-for-featured-snippets"></div>
<h3>5. Optimize for featured snippets and AI Overviews</h3>
<p>If your content is a wall of text, it‚Äôs like handing over a puzzle with missing pieces. But if you break things up with clear headings, short paragraphs, and easy-to-read lists, you‚Äôre basically spoon-feeding the AI exactly what it wants to show users.</p>
<p>Look at the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-overviews-breaking-search">AI Overview</a> for the query ‚ÄúWhat size hose do I need for my yard?‚Äù It‚Äôs all bite-sized information with headings and lists. You can‚Äôt argue that it‚Äôs not organized. Or not straight to the point.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/ai-overview-result-garden-hose-png.webp" alt="ai overview for search around garden hoses" width="876" height="845" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-90008" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/ai-overview-result-garden-hose-png.webp 876w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/ai-overview-result-garden-hose-480x463.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 876px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Here‚Äôs how to optimize for those kinds of results:</p>
<ul>
<li>Answer the intent of the query without any fluff. AI is going to concisely give users the information they want, so you should too. Get to the point right away.</li>
<li>Use H1s, H2s, and H3s properly. Your main heading (H1) should set the stage, while subheadings (H2s and H3s) break content into logical sections. You can even go H4 and beyond if the content is deep enough to warrant that.</li>
<li>Put sets of bite-sized information in bullet points, like this very set you‚Äôre reading now.</li>
<li>Put sequences and steps into numbered lists.</li>
</ul>
<p>By structuring your content with AI crawlers in mind, you‚Äôre increasing the odds of getting featured in AI-driven results and attracting human visitors to your site.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f680.png" alt="üöÄ" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>Want to learn how AI can supercharge your ads strategy?</strong> Free guide &gt;&gt; <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/resources/ai-advertising?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_AIAdvertising_Download&amp;itm_source=wordstream&amp;itm_medium=blog&amp;itm_campaign=incontent_links">9 Powerful Ways to Use AI in Google &amp; Facebook Ads</a></p>
<div id="adapt-content-strategy-for-ai-platforms"></div>
<h3>6. Adapt your content strategy for specific AI platforms</h3>
<p>Pay attention to <em>how</em> the various AI platforms respond and <em>what</em> they respond with. Tailor your content to those characteristics.</p>
<p>For example, when I start searching on Perplexity, it provides auto-suggestions. And when I search ‚Äúproject management for,‚Äù this is what comes up:</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/perplexity-auto-suggestions-example-png.webp" alt="auto suggestion example on perplexity" width="675" height="521" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-90009" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/perplexity-auto-suggestions-example-png.webp 675w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/perplexity-auto-suggestions-example-480x370.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 675px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>If you‚Äôre <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/target-audience-examples">targeting certain types of businesses</a>, this can be a goldmine of ideas to create content around. Experiment with your target keywords to see what comes up.</p>
<p>Perplexity also produces related questions at the very end of its responses. You could create content that answers these exact questions. These are the questions that appeared at the end of ‚Äúproject management for engineers:&#8221;</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/perplexity-related-questions-example-png.webp" alt="example of related questions on perplexity search" width="658" height="296" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-90010" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/perplexity-related-questions-example-png.webp 658w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/perplexity-related-questions-example-480x216.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 658px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>As another example, take ChatGPT.</p>
<p>Chris Long of Go Fish Digital <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/chris-long-marketing_seo-tip-take-the-queries-youre-tracking-activity-7288185314395725824-ya_0" target="_blank" rel="noopener">shared a post on LinkedIn</a>, suggesting you search your target keywords in ChatGPT (one at a time) to see which ones trigger the search function.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/search-function-triggered-on-chatgpt.webp" alt="example of query where search function was triggered on chatgpt" width="1280" height="1972" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-90011" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/search-function-triggered-on-chatgpt.webp 1280w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/search-function-triggered-on-chatgpt-980x1510.webp 980w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/search-function-triggered-on-chatgpt-480x740.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1280px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/chris-long-marketing_seo-tip-take-the-queries-youre-tracking-activity-7288185314395725824-ya_0" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Source</a></em></p>
<p>Once you learn which ones trigger a search response (as opposed to chat), look at the type of results. Are they listicles? Are they comparison pieces?</p>
<p>Take inspiration from what‚Äôs there and build a strategy to optimize for those on your site.</p>
<div id="how-to-track-ai-referral-traffic"></div>
<h2>How to track site traffic from AI search</h2>
<p>Naturally, you should monitor the traffic you get from AI to see:</p>
<ul>
<li>Which platforms bring you the most traffic.</li>
<li>The types of content that are most effective for getting AI traffic.</li>
<li>The topics generate the best quality AI traffic‚Äìlook at conversions, time on site, etc.</li>
</ul>
<p>If you use <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/02/17/ga4-features-for-advertisers">GA4</a>, here‚Äôs how to identify traffic from a few of the platforms:</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/tracking-generative-ai-traffic-ga4-png.webp" alt="chart showing generative ai tracking in ga4" width="1429" height="1143" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-90012" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/tracking-generative-ai-traffic-ga4-png.webp 1429w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/tracking-generative-ai-traffic-ga4-1280x1024.webp 1280w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/tracking-generative-ai-traffic-ga4-980x784.webp 980w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/tracking-generative-ai-traffic-ga4-480x384.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) and (max-width: 1280px) 1280px, (min-width: 1281px) 1429px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://www.seerinteractive.com/insights/are-ai-sites-like-chatgpt-sending-your-website-traffic" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Source</a></em></p>
<p>I recommend creating a custom channel group, which will allow you to easily compare data against other channels like organic search, direct, etc.</p>
<p>Skip down to steps 3 and 4 in Nico Brooks‚Äô guide, <a href="https://twooctobers.com/blog/tracking-ai-traffic-in-ga4-a-step-by-step-guide/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Tracking AI Traffic in GA4</a>, to see how you can do this. It‚Äôs easier than you think!</p>
<p>And then you can break things down from there, by source (AI platform), by landing page, etc.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/ga4-ai-traffic-source-png.webp" alt="ai traffic as a source in ga4" width="401" height="599" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-90014" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/ga4-ai-traffic-source-png.webp 401w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/ga4-ai-traffic-source-201x300.webp 201w" sizes="(max-width: 401px) 100vw, 401px" /></p>
